metadata.exif:ImageDescription: KAITAIA, NEW ZEALAND - NOVEMBER 26:  Mana Party Leader Hone Harawira is welcomed by his party faithful as New Zealanders go to the polls during the 2011 General Election on November 26, 2011 in Kaitaia, New Zealand. Today's triumphant candidate will lead New Zealand's 50th Parliament, with the Labour Party and Opposition's Phil Goff considered the key challenger to current National Party Prime Minister John Key.  (Photo by Kenny Rodger/Getty Images)
